Here's the approach:

### 1. Define three `ResourceDictionary` files

Create one per theme (e.g., `LightTheme.xaml`, `DarkTheme.xaml`, `HighContrastTheme.xaml`) with matching keys:

```xml
<!-- Resources/Styles/LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="PrimaryText">#1A1A1A</Color>
    <Color x:Key="Accent">#0078D4</Color>
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Repeat for `DarkTheme.xaml` and `HighContrastTheme.xaml` with different values.

### 2. Create a theme service

```csharp
public enum AppTheme { Light, Dark, HighContrast }

public static class ThemeService
{
    public static void ApplyTheme(AppTheme theme)
    {
        var mergedDicts = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;

        // Remove the current theme dictionary (always last entry)
        if (mergedDicts.LastOrDefault() is ResourceDictionary old
            && old is LightTheme or DarkTheme or HighContrastTheme)
        {
            mergedDicts.Remove(old);
        }

        ResourceDictionary next = theme switch
        {
            AppTheme.Dark         => new DarkTheme(),
            AppTheme.HighContrast => new HighContrastTheme(),
            _                     => new LightTheme()
        };

        mergedDicts.Add(next);

        // Persist the choice
        Preferences.Set("app_theme", theme.ToString());
    }

    public static AppTheme LoadSavedTheme() =>
        Enum.TryParse(Preferences.Get("app_theme", "Light"), out AppTheme t)
            ? t : AppTheme.Light;
}
```

### 3. Apply on startup in `App.xaml.cs`

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(ThemeService.LoadSavedTheme());
}
```

### 4. Reference theme colors with `DynamicResource`

This is critical — `StaticResource` won't update at runtime:

```xml
<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource PageBackground}">
    <Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryText}" Text="Hello" />
</ContentPage>
```

### 5. Settings page picker

```xml
<Picker x:Name="ThemePicker" Title="Theme"
        ItemsSource="{Binding Themes}"
        SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedTheme}"
        SelectedIndexChanged="OnThemeChanged" />
```

```csharp
void OnThemeChanged(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    if (ThemePicker.SelectedItem is string name
        && Enum.TryParse(name, out AppTheme theme))
    {
        ThemeService.ApplyTheme(theme);
    }
}
```

### Key points

| Concept | Why it matters |
|---|---|
| `DynamicResource` | Allows live swap without restarting |
| `MergedDictionaries` | Swap the entire dictionary in one shot |
| `Preferences` | Persists the user's choice across sessions |
| Matching keys | All three dictionaries must use identical `x:Key` names |

This gives you instant, app-wide theme switching with no page reloads.
